    <prp:abstract>This program aims to detect and characterize the circumstellar dust found around the hot (110,000 K) white dwarf in the Helix Nebula in the millimeter to test two competing hypotheses for its origin: (1) a scaled-down post-AGB binary disk or (2) a rejuvenated debris disk resulting from collisions among surviving planetesimals. In the former case, the millimeter emission is expected to be compact; while the millimeter emission in the latter case can be resolved by ALMA's superior resolution. If the latter case is confirmed, the ALMA observation will provide the first resolved image of an exoplanetary system that has survived the demise of its host star.</prp:abstract>
